									<h1>Loop Review - Focus on for()</h1>
									<p>You can think of a loop as a computerized version of the game where you tell someone to take X steps in one direction then Y steps in another; for example, the idea "Go five steps to the east" could be expressed this way as a loop - Modzilla Developer Docs</p>
									<pre>
										<code class="language-javascript">
											//Breakdown of the for condition: 
											// for ([initialExpression]; [condition]; [incrementExpression])
											var step;
											for (step = 0; step < 5; step++) {
											  // Runs 5 times, with values of step 0 through 4.
											  console.log('Walking east one step');
											}
										</code>
									</pre>
								</section>

